Let f(x)=10π sin^2 x − 4x. On any interval [α,β] where 4x < 10π sin^2 x the corresponding segment of y=4x has length (β−α)√17. Hence total length = √17 · (total x-measure of {x≥0 : f(x)>0}).

f is positive only for x∈[0,5π/2], has zeros symmetric about 5π/4, and is positive exactly on three symmetric intervals whose total x-measure equals 5π/4. Therefore the total length is √17·(5π/4).

\boxed{\dfrac{5\pi\sqrt{17}}{4}}
